spans.text: whirlwind , hail and frost , Fierce winter
more the breezes waft presume , No more the warbling waters roll : Deserts of snow fatigue the eye , Black storms
the warm bowl and ruddy fire
While mute and shrinking with her fears
the hearth she sits alone : At morn her bridegroom went abroad , The night is dark and deep the road ; She sighs and wishes him at home
All fresh with dews and opening
How soon before thy vernal ray Should each unkindly damp
How soon before thy vernal ray Should each unkindly damp
The indulgence of the sovereign cause
if the gay , well-natured friend Bids leave the studious page awhile
while the genial glass is paid By each to her
! thou delight of heaven and earth , When will thy happy morn arise
while she walks the wonted grove
the ONE primaeval fair , Thither , you silver
if believing love can read The wonted softness in her eye
